Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.41,0:00:03.30,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.11,0:00:03.30,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.09,0:00:09.83,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Alright, let's say hi to everyone before we leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.83,0:00:10.60,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.60,0:00:11.98,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Ah, we got the stamp!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.98,0:00:14.60,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Let's use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.17,0:00:13.84,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,810)}Need to use it. Need to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:14.60,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,810)}Need to use it x2
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:16.31,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}"Let's stay together", everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:24.20,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}We're pretty buried under all the other stamps,\Nbut I really am using mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.20,0:00:27.76,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Well then, everyone, thanks for watching with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:29.85,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Time to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:29.85,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,810)}See you~.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:32.27,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Thanks for watching with us.
Comment: 0,0:00:33.72,0:00:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,~~~ BEGIN REAL AFTERLIVE AFTERTALK ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.21,0:00:36.72,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.21,0:00:36.72,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:41.42,Ena,,0,0,0,,So with that, the Afterlive was so good, wasn't it? The song too of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.42,0:00:50.30,Ena,,0,0,0,,That and the talk segments, I was so glad to see everyone getting back to normal after everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.30,0:00:53.39,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thanks for watching with us, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.21,0:00:53.39,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.39,0:01:01.05,Ena,,0,0,0,,So that was the first Afterlive performance of "Yoka ni Mitorete",
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.05,0:01:04.38,Ena,,0,0,0,,so I think there may be a few first-time listeners here,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.38,0:01:12.46,Ena,,0,0,0,,as well maybe some who've already seen the 2D and 3D MVs that've been out since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.46,0:01:16.66,Ena,,0,0,0,,Come on. It's just so good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.66,0:01:20.93,Ena,,0,0,0,,Just simply a wonderful song.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.93,0:01:27.13,Ena,,0,0,0,,"Yoka ni Mitorete".... For Ena, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.13,0:01:32.33,Ena,,0,0,0,,these are the words with which she's turning to face Mizuki and saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.33,0:01:38.49,Ena,,0,0,0,,Like the lyrics say, she's just holding onto Mizuki....
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.50,0:01:42.13,Ena,,0,0,0,,Holding onto Mizuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.13,0:01:46.31,Ena,,0,0,0,,so gently, and on the verge of tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.31,0:01:55.18,Ena,,0,0,0,,N25 songs often have lots of painful or negative emotions in their lyrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.18,0:01:59.72,Ena,,0,0,0,,but now that everyone is moving forward little by little in their own journeys,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:03.52,Ena,,0,0,0,,they can voice more than just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.52,0:02:07.55,Ena,,0,0,0,,That's why they could sing this song.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.55,0:02:15.23,Ena,,0,0,0,,So actually, keeno-san was able to participate remotely in our recording sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:25.38,Ena,,0,0,0,,They supported each of us in our four recording sessions by voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.38,0:02:32.16,Ena,,0,0,0,,But weren't they such a warm and gentle person, just like their song?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:38.49,Ena,,0,0,0,,I thought, "Makes sense that such a gentle person was able to make such a gentle song."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.49,0:02:43.81,Ena,,0,0,0,,And then we were able to watch the 2DMV and 3DMV for the first time yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.81,0:02:53.07,Ena,,0,0,0,,We were able to see Bouno-san's wonderful illustrations in so many different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.07,0:02:59.89,Ena,,0,0,0,,You can really tell how much respect for the story they put in the MVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.89,0:03:04.02,Ena,,0,0,0,,Please do watch them, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.67,0:03:04.03,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Please watch to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:05.34,Ena,,0,0,0,,They're both flower-themed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:05.87,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:07.08,Ena,,0,0,0,,"Yoka ni Mitorete",
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:07.08,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960.381,960)}"Admiring the Late-Blooming Flowers"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:08.94,Ena,,0,0,0,,and "Bake no Hana."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:08.94,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1008.763,960)}"Monstrous Flower"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.94,0:03:12.93,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,During our recording sessions, we asked if they coordinated that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.93,0:03:17.19,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,but it was actually completely unplanned that both titles would have the word "flower".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.19,0:03:23.82,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,We always provide a— what is it— the story prototype to the vocaloid producers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.82,0:03:28.44,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,and both ended up coming up with a song about "flowers".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.44,0:03:31.23,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,I think that was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:32.14,Ena,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.14,0:03:36.10,Ena,,0,0,0,,They didn't connect the titles like that on purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:39.37,Ena,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's a reason for it, but it's not like they coordinated this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.37,0:03:40.45,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Complete coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.45,0:03:42.99,Ena,,0,0,0,,It felt like it was almost a fated coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.99,0:03:46.26,Ena,,0,0,0,,One that made a wonderfully connected story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:51.92,Ena,,0,0,0,,We got so much reaction to "Bake no Hana" too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:56.70,Ena,,0,0,0,,Even the singing distribution was— how to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:04:00.63,Ena,,0,0,0,,it reminds you a lot of the story, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.63,0:04:04.83,Ena,,0,0,0,,Even the fact that Ena has relatively few parts might have some grounding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:07.21,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,It did, didn't it? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.45,0:04:07.21,Ena,,0,0,0,,It did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.21,0:04:11.89,Ena,,0,0,0,,Please, do listen to both songs if you haven't already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.89,0:04:22.97,Ena,,0,0,0,,So once again, both the 2DMV and the 3DMV are available to watch on the official ProSeka YouTube channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:28.07,Ena,,0,0,0,,so maybe after this Aftertalk, please watch as many times as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.07,0:04:32.28,Ena,,0,0,0,,Both are really good in their own ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.28,0:04:35.72,Ena,,0,0,0,,So please do if you have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.72,0:04:36.38,Ena,,0,0,0,,Moving on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:45.03,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Alright then, we also have 5 new cards to introduce as well today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.03,0:04:48.97,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Have you already seen the card art and side stories, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:50.12,Ena,,0,0,0,,Alright...
Comment: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:50.12,Note,,0,0,0,,~~~ BEGIN CARD ART SEGMENT ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.12,0:04:51.22,Ena,,0,0,0,,Hinata will show us the cards and I'll go over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.22,0:04:53.72,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Hinata will show us the cards and I'll go over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.62,0:04:52.52,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}First up...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.72,0:04:56.67,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}we'll start with Ena Shinonome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.67,0:04:57.67,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}It's Ena~.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.67,0:05:00.45,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.37,0:05:00.45,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}Untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:03.34,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}We saw this art in the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.34,0:05:04.68,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Such warm colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:07.88,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}And next, the trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:10.13,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}So good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.69,0:05:10.13,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.13,0:05:11.67,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:14.32,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Shall we move to the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.32,0:05:14.97,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Next up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.97,0:05:18.03,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Akiyama Mizuki, untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.03,0:05:19.17,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:23.29,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}This one also appeared in the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.29,0:05:25.32,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}In that beautiful scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:27.69,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}And this is the trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.69,0:05:34.83,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}I want to line them all up on my wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:36.62,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.62,0:05:37.83,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Now for MEIKO.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:40.40,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:44.26,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}MEIKO really did work hard in this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:46.98,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Endlessly grateful to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.66,0:05:46.98,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}So grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.98,0:05:48.15,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Man,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.15,0:05:49.41,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}just so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:50.98,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Haha indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.98,0:05:54.44,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Next up is the trained art.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.44,0:05:57.55,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}So good we get to see so many different angles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.55,0:06:00.92,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Long-hair MEIKO is so pretty too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:03.79,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}So pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.79,0:06:06.18,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}The flowers look so good on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.04,0:06:06.20,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}They do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:08.33,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Next up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:11.21,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Let's move to Kanade, untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.21,0:06:15.24,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Uhh... untrained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:17.08,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}She's eating her cup ramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:19.78,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}She is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.78,0:06:23.58,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}That's Kanade's untrained, next we have the trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:26.97,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Her hair is so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.97,0:06:28.86,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}So true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:38.16,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,50)}Note: Yes yes yes yes please go watch it if you haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:35.12,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}By the way, if you haven't checked\Nout Kanade's side story yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:38.16,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}I think you might enjoy the story more if you read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:41.75,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}If you've been playing the event\Nand have points saved up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.75,0:06:44.16,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}I think you can still exchange for her up till today,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.16,0:06:46.53,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}so please do get this card.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:47.45,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Next up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.45,0:06:47.85,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.85,0:06:48.46,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.46,0:06:50.01,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Mafuyu.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.71,0:06:50.01,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,820)}Mafuyu.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:51.27,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}You long press it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.27,0:06:53.27,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.27,0:06:55.52,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Mafuyu-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:06:59.53,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Mafuyu also helped out a lot this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.53,0:07:06.16,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Right? I was really glad to hear\Nsuch warm words coming from Mafuyu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.16,0:07:08.86,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}I always really like her expressions in these.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.58,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Please admire every detail, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.58,0:07:13.67,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Please do, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.67,0:07:14.58,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Aren't these so good?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:17.12,Ena - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:21.05,Mizuki - Subscreen,,0,0,0,,{\pos(650,750)}Last time's illustrations had\Na lot more of a muted palette,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.05,0:07:25.43,Ena,,0,0,0,,but these ones feature a lot more vivid, yet warm and gentle hues.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.43,0:07:27.93,Ena,,0,0,0,,Both have their good points,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:33.73,Ena,,0,0,0,,but I feel like this gentler style really fit the progression of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:37.91,Ena,,0,0,0,,Alright, so with that, it was just a short time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:43.75,Ena,,0,0,0,,but that's all for the ProSeka Aftertalk "With Our Wounded Hands" Edition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.75,0:07:47.16,Ena,,0,0,0,,What did you think, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:53.65,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching, and for all the warm comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.65,0:07:59.08,Ena,,0,0,0,,With that, we'll each make some closing remarks about today's stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:01.16,Ena,,0,0,0,,Take it away, Hinata-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:05.69,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for watching, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:13.90,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Right. For me, I think that the best way I can "face" Mizuki is through my acting,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.90,0:08:20.39,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,and while I think it might be a bit presumptuous to say that I fully met her feelings with my acting,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:26.04,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,I did all that I could to put my absolute everything into recording in that booth that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.04,0:08:33.55,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,And you know... for voice acting in games like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.55,0:08:39.00,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,you have to leave pauses between lines for the player to tap through.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.00,0:08:42.15,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,That's... a pretty common sense way of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.15,0:08:45.26,Ena,,0,0,0,,The editors would have to cut out each line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.96,0:08:45.26,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they'd have to cut out each line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:49.83,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,That'd normally be the case, but for these performances with lots of crying—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.83,0:08:51.54,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,how to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.54,0:08:54.55,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,you can't really cut yourself short.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:09:01.16,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,So I asked Colorful Palette if it'd be fine to record this all in one continuous take.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:06.77,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Like, "could you cut this part out?" or "could you cut my crying or sniffling here out?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:08.97,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,That way I can keep the emotions flowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.97,0:09:10.55,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,And they were very understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.55,0:09:17.35,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,And when I saw the final cut, I thought they did an amazing job editing everything together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.35,0:09:24.85,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,I could tell that Colorful Palette took a lot of the emotions I put into my acting into the editing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:27.50,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,You can really tell if you look at the game data.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:29.91,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,So— how to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.91,0:09:33.18,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Though I am watching over Mizuki as the one voicing her,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.18,0:09:38.38,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,there's still a lot in store for all the N25 members,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:43.54,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,like their careers, songwriting, and other challenges ahead of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:47.36,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Even if I'm not directly helping them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.36,0:09:54.19,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,maybe from the shadows, I hope I can continue to gently support the N25 members.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:57.08,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for watching today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.08,0:09:59.25,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Over to Minori-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:02.95,Ena,,0,0,0,,Ehh, thank you very much everyone for watching all the way to the end today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.95,0:10:10.26,Ena,,0,0,0,,For this story— this story and the previous one, especially both Chapter 8s,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.26,0:10:14.14,Ena,,0,0,0,,we received so many comments from those who—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.14,0:10:21.45,Ena,,0,0,0,,those who were moved, or how the story really made them think.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.45,0:10:29.98,Ena,,0,0,0,,But truly, those moments only happen because of the long journey these characters have walked to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.98,0:10:34.97,Ena,,0,0,0,,We only watched Chapter 8 today, but if you look at the whole story from Chapter 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.97,0:10:38.97,Ena,,0,0,0,,the characters are always challenging themselves or grappling with their issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.97,0:10:40.80,Ena,,0,0,0,,That’s what makes them possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.99,Ena,,0,0,0,,Ena and Mizuki being able to move forward together is, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.99,0:10:50.50,Ena,,0,0,0,,only possible thanks to their bonds and interactions with the other members.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.50,0:10:57.62,Ena,,0,0,0,,So I really hope everyone watches every single Chapter without skipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.62,0:11:02.68,Ena,,0,0,0,,to truly feel what the characters are going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:07.47,Ena,,0,0,0,,As for Ena's growth, after all this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.47,0:11:13.60,Ena,,0,0,0,,Ena was able to get through to Mizuki— maybe not completely yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.60,0:11:19.07,Ena,,0,0,0,,but Ena was able to do this thanks to her ability to face feelings with art.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:22.78,Ena,,0,0,0,,Through all the growth she went through in all the previous stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:26.63,Ena,,0,0,0,,she's mature enough to see things through someone else's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.63,0:11:33.12,Ena,,0,0,0,,and that's what helped both Mizuki and Ena move forward in this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:36.83,Ena,,0,0,0,,N25 were able to face one of their problems together,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.83,0:11:43.53,Ena,,0,0,0,,but for Ena personally, with her painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.53,0:11:46.71,Ena,,0,0,0,,she hasn't quite reached her goal yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.71,0:11:49.83,Ena,,0,0,0,,In Ena's last focus event story,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.83,0:11:54.60,Ena,,0,0,0,,there were some comments saying she's gotten over her issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.03,Ena,,0,0,0,,but personally, I don’t see it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:12:02.79,Ena,,0,0,0,,I feel like this is just the beginning of an endless road towards the artist she's striving to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.79,0:12:06.36,Ena,,0,0,0,,So, thank you, truly, to everyone who supports her on that journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.36,0:12:13.58,Ena,,0,0,0,,I’ll continue from here forward taking responsibility for Ena’s life,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:16.81,Ena,,0,0,0,,and do my absolute best to carry her life forward as an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.81,0:12:17.32,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:18.95,Ena,,0,0,0,,So with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.07,0:12:18.95,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:20.68,Ena,,0,0,0,,that's all we have for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.68,0:12:22.23,Ena,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.23,0:12:30.90,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(965.333,156.667)}Bro if you haven't watch Ena5 yet what the heck are you doing hahaha
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.23,0:12:26.29,Ena,,0,0,0,,Those of you who haven't watched the story, once the next event starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.29,0:12:27.80,Ena,,0,0,0,,it'll be on—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.81,0:12:27.80,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,YouTube?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.80,0:12:29.49,Ena,,0,0,0,,On YouTube?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.49,0:12:30.90,Ena,,0,0,0,,Ah, in-game?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.90,0:12:35.98,Ena,,0,0,0,,You can watch it freely in-game, so please do so if you couldn't unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:38.76,Ena,,0,0,0,,It should also be uploaded to YouTube,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:38.76,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.76,0:12:41.08,Ena,,0,0,0,,so please watch it there if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.08,0:12:44.32,Ena,,0,0,0,,So with that, we're at the end of our program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:47.32,Ena,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's too early to say "Happy New Year?" For Project Sekai?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.32,0:12:50.68,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,"Happy New Year"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.68,0:12:53.28,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Well, the staff still have a lot of recording left to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:12:56.28,Ena,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all the staff we're seeing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.45,0:12:56.28,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Staff members,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.28,0:12:58.87,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,thanks for the continued support. Maybe more fitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.87,0:13:03.38,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,But for everyone watching, we wish you a happy new year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.38,0:13:06.33,Ena,,0,0,0,,On SekaRaji, I did the same thing, thinking it was too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.33,0:13:08.13,Ena,,0,0,0,,We just recorded it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.13,0:13:12.31,Ena,,0,0,0,,Well, either way, have a happy new year, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.31,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Happy new year, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:15.56,Ena,,0,0,0,,We look forward to another great year with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.56,0:13:17.50,Ena,,0,0,0,,See you again next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.50,0:13:18.64,Ena,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.20,0:13:21.70,Mizuki,,0,0,0,,Bye bye~
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.64,0:13:21.70,Ena,,0,0,0,,Bye bye~
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:23.50,Ena,,0,0,0,,
